setAttribute

protected boolean setAttribute(java.lang.String propertie,
                               java.lang.String valueStr,
                               PhysicalObjectType physicalObjectType)
check if the property is an attribute in JAXB and set it notice: if valueStr not convertible to a double (e.g. it is from a boolean or from a string), then return false; that means, if there in the future an attribute that isn't a double, we have to handle it explicit

Parameters:
propertie - - is the name of the property
valueStr - - is the value of the property as a String
physicalObjectTyp - - the JaxB object
Returns:
true - if is an Attribute, otherwise false
